The paper discusses a system for querying relational databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The system uses natural language interfaces (cs.CL) and programming-by-example (cs.AI) to allow users to express their queries in alternative ways. The paper also discusses user studies and simulations, which involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE) aspects.
